            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>and your<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato & basil sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and roughly shred</p>",
